# SaneProcess compliance manifest
name: SaneClick
type: macos_app
scheme: SaneClick
project: SaneClick.xcodeproj
bundle_id: com.saneclick.SaneClick

build:
  xcodegen: true

release:
  team_id: M78L6FXD48
  signing_identity: "Developer ID Application"
  dist_host: dist.saneclick.com
  site_host: saneclick.com
  r2_bucket: sanebar-downloads
  use_sparkle: true
  min_system_version: "14.0"
  reviewed_auto_reconcile_stashes:
    - stash_sha: "22f0f9c46e2e4ac5b806f47a77c264fb9b2058eb"
      subject: "On main: auto-reconcile-20260508-215519-stephans-mac-mini"
      decision: superseded
      reason: "Reviewed 2026-05-09. Key runtime files revert HEAD away from the live 1.1.6 direct-download state: .saneprocess flips App Store back on, menu/settings routing loses current Settings/License/About access patterns, and release metadata/docs regress. Current HEAD already carries the intended menu parity and direct-download behavior."
    - stash_sha: "dc659a6b51b6b5fe5fafb8b8db51b06eb490389c"
      subject: "On main: auto-reconcile-20260501-215526-stephans-macbook-air"
      decision: recovered
      reason: "Reviewed 2026-05-11. The stash only adds first_value_action analytics in ScriptExecutor; current HEAD already contains that analytics hook and later replaces the stale file-watcher startup path with launch-request-scoped execution handling, so no unique release work remains."
    - stash_sha: "b8bb31a8e4f8295c455e88b13d9d8aabe3ffaad1"
      subject: "On main: auto-reconcile-20260425-215520-stephans-mac-mini"
      decision: superseded
      reason: "Reviewed 2026-05-09. Docs/README residue is older than the live release: docs/index.html points back to 1.1.5 download URLs and README says Dock/menu bar visibility is fully independent, which conflicts with the current 1.1.6 behavior that preserves at least one access point."
    - stash_sha: "57a6709456963c7341533741c4c891e2f1fb0b07"
      subject: "On main: auto-reconcile-20260424-215517-stephans-mac-mini"
      decision: superseded
      reason: "Reviewed 2026-05-09. Website copy is stale and conflicts with current release docs: it reverts to 1.1.5 links and older Public Code wording, while HEAD/live docs use the current 1.1.6 direct-download links and Transparent Code positioning."
    - stash_sha: "d57327aadd1d8b4937340f4ef4f9b36f1347e688"
      subject: "On main: auto-reconcile-20260417-055518-stephans-mac-mini"
      decision: deferred
      reason: "Reviewed 2026-05-09. This stash is App Store screenshot/storyboard collateral plus older 1.1.5 project metadata. SaneClick current release lane is direct-download-only with appstore disabled in .saneprocess, so this work is not part of the live 1.1.6 release candidate."
    - stash_sha: "42ad70538ed01a3c05cfddb8a16b1fafb8e4afb6"
      subject: "On main: auto-reconcile-20260416-215512-stephans-mac-mini"
